/* Health and lifestyle */ I looked high and low, but I couldn't find definitive evidence on her having been a smoker for the majority of her life, e.g. medical sources. Given the (scientifically established) low likelihood of a smoker surviving to become the oldest person in the world, it seems more likely that a tobacco company 'sponsored' her late-life smoking for the positive publicity, and for this reason any claims about her 'lifelong smoking habits' should be viewed with suspicion.
